This paper deals with machine learning and optimization techniques for binary classification. The paper discusses the use of logistic loss as a surrogate loss function for optimizing approximate median significance (AMS). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper also discusses computer vision techniques for binary classification, which makes cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses statistical techniques for binary classification, which makes cs.ST (Statistics) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of optimization techniques for binary classification, which makes cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) another possible sub-category.
